# Files executed inside Linux containers must stay LF even when checked out on
# Windows (core.autocrlf=true). A CRLF shebang makes the kernel look for an
# interpreter like `/bin/sh\r`, which exec()s fail with the misleading
# "No such file or directory" — the container then exits before serving.
*.sh        text eol=lf
Dockerfile  text eol=lf
Dockerfile.* text eol=lf
entrypoint.sh text eol=lf
